Usage: write_spd [-help] -file <string> [{-nets <net>+ | -selected } [-cut_margin <float>] [-with_shield ]]

-help                   # Prints out the command usage
-cut_margin <float>     # Specified the cut margin expanded from specified nets
                        # bounding box.The -cut_margin option must be used with
                        # the -nets or -selected options (float, required)
-file <string>          # Specify the spd file name. (string, required)
-nets <net>+            # Specified named nets. If you specify one net name,
                        # you do not need the braces around the name.
                        # ((net)+, optional)
-selected               # Specified selected nets. Select nets using the
                        # select_obj command. (bool, optional)
-with_shield            # By default, write_spd does not consider the
                        # completeness of shielding when generate the SPD file
                        # of selected nets. When -with_shield is specified,
                        # write_spd generate shielding routing (if any) of the
                        # specified nets. (bool, optional)